LAMMPS stands for Large-scale Atomic/Molecular Massively Parallel
Simulator.

This LAMMPS 99 version has been superceded by more current versions.
See the <A HREF="http://www.cs.sandia.gov/~sjplimp/lammps.html">LAMMPS
WWW Site</A> for more information.

LAMMPS is a classical molecular dynamics simulation code designed to
run efficiently on parallel computers.  It was developed at Sandia
National Laboratories, a US Department of Energy facility, with
funding from the DOE.

The primary author and contact for LAMMPS is Steve Plimpton, who can
be contacted at sjplimp@sandia.gov.  The LAMMPS WWW page is at
www.cs.sandia.gov/~sjplimp/lammps.html.

The LAMMPS 99 distribution includes the following files and directories:

README			this file
LICENSE			the GNU General Public License (GPL)
doc			documentation
src			source code
examples		test problems and output
tools			additional pre- and post-processing tools
msi2lmp			tool for converting to/from LAMMPS format

See the doc/README.html file for information on how to make and use
LAMMPS.
